The paper focuses on improving data quality and diversity in dialog systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses neural networks for sentence embeddings and distance-based outlier detection, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses data collection and mining, which falls under the category of information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a technique for improving model robustness, which falls under the category of systems and control (SI). Therefore, cs.SI (Systems and Control) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
